    "body": "I think there are two different things here. One is about imports, and this is independent of the package manager: if you are requiring/importing `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox`, then you don't need to import any of the plugins that it includes. If you get a typescript error, then that might be a configuration problem (normally the `tsconfig.json` file has some issue).\r\n\r\nThen, with respect to package managers: I think only npm 7+ automatically installs peer dependencies. AFAIK pnpm does too but it's an opt-in option that you have to enable with `pnpm config set auto-install-peers true`.\r\n\r\n@SvenMeyer If that doesn't answer your question, I'm gonna need you to be more specific about what your problem is and, if possible, to create a reproduction example.",
